@node Ref_Numbers "Number Systems"
@{fg highlight}Number Systems
--------------@{fg text}

Decimal (Base 10)

  1000 100  10   1
     |   |   |	 |

     9   5   3   6


   9 x 1000 = 9000
   5 x  100 =  500
   3 x   10 =   30
   6 x    1 = +  6
             -----
              9536

Hexadecimal (Base 16)

  4096 256  16   1
     |   |   |   |

     3   C   2   B

   3 x 4096 = 12288
  12 x  256 =  3072
   2 x   16 =    32
  11 x    1 = +  11
              -----
              15403


Binary (Base 2)

   128 64 32 16  8  4  2  1
     |  |  |  |  |  |  |  |

     1  1  0  0  1  1  1  0

   1 x 128 = 128
   1 x  64 =  64
   0 x  32 =   0
   0 x  16 =   0
   1 x   8 =   8
   1 x   4 =   4
   1 x   2 = + 2
            ----
             206
@endnode
@node Revisions "Previous versions"
@{fg highlight}Previous versions
------------------------@{fg text}
- Module format has changed. Delete all modules and recompile them.

- 'NoteRange' parameter implemented for 'Define Device'.

- Updated documentation.

- Added reference sections to the documentation.

- 'MANUFACTURER' and 'DEVICE' options implemented for 'Text'.

- Fixed a bug in the ReadToolTypes routine that would cause an Enforcer
  hit when run from the CLI.

- Implemented 'Position2' alternative for Links.

- Implemented 'Link Type Note'.

- Implemented 'Gadget Type Button'.

- All prefs files changed to non-binary format. Delete all old .prefs
  files.

- All prefs files are now created in one prefs directory.

- Added a script to delete all modules. Requires C:IconX, C:List,
  C:Delete and Execute. It will only delete module files (.mse), not
  default midi patches (.dm).

- Added camd.library support.

- Changed 'Gadget Type MX - LabelPlace' default to RIGHT.

- All ToolTypes can now be used as parameters when used from the CLI.

- Tooltype 'Definition' added.

- Tooltype 'ErrorLog' added.

- Added a script to compile all modules. Requires C:IconX, RX, C:List,
  C:Delete and Execute. It will only compile definition files with names
  ending with ".def".

- Implemented prefs/MSE.prefs file for configuration of memory usage.

@{fg highlight}
---------@{fg text}

- Implemented 'Gadget Type MX'.

- Fixed errors in documentation.

- Module format has changed. Delete all modules and recompile them.

- Replaced 'Border RECESS' option with a more powerful 'Frame' parameter.

- All prefs files moved into prefs directory.

- Tooltype 'Font' added.

@{fg highlight}
---------@{fg text}

- Now remembers the last path and definition compiled. The File
  requester defaults to these.

- Tooltype 'Last' added.

- 'Define Palette ()' implemented.

- Module format has changed. Delete all modules and recompile them.

- 'DragBar' option implemented for 'Define Window ()'

- Tooltypes 'WindowL' and 'WindowT' added.

@{fg highlight}
---------@{fg text}

- Module format has changed. Delete all modules and recompile them.

- Modules directory is created if it does not exist.

- Fixed error in 'Last' tooltype processing.

- Fixed bug in WB ToolType processing.

- Increased maximum value for MaxChannel to 32.

- Fixed bug in handling of filenames.

- 'Last' tooltype usage modified.

- Window no longer activated when opened.

- Window now sensitive to system font height.

- <name> now error checked for spaces.

- Implemented 'Link Type ARexx'.

@{fg highlight}
---------@{fg text}
- Module format has changed. Delete all modules and recompile them.

- The link for the root command 'Define Initialize' was missing from this
  documention. It's now there.

- Improved handling of strings which led to string corruption in MSE.

- Documented 'LevelText' for 'Link Type Numbers'.

- Documented 'LevelText' and 'Default' for 'Gadget Type Slider'.

- Better handles Project icon invocations.

- Properly locks directory when processing icon tooltypes.

- Fixed error in processing of 'Link Type ARexx' and a bug which could
  have caused 680x0 Exception errors.

- Module windows (Non-DragBar) are no longer backdrop windows. Did you
  even know that they were?  This caused problems with the new PubScreen
  featue of MSE. This makes modules 2 bytes per window smaller.

@{fg highlight}
---------@{fg text}

- Module format has changed. Delete all modules and recompile them.

- Implemented 'XBitsOffset' for 'Midi Data <method>'. Allows split value
  storage.

- Implemented 'Gadget Type List'.

- Updated documentation.


@{fg highlight}97.Jul.10
---------@{fg text}

- Fixed the "//" bug in the file requester, which caused the compiler to
  exit without compiling sometimes.

- Handles 'File not found' errors properly.

- Fixed a 68000-020 bug which would cause Numeric Definition errors where
  they didn't exist.

- Implemented 'Define Data' for sharing gadget data. As an example of
  the greatness of this: the Matrix-6R module was 27738 bytes before
  using shared gadget data, and 17554 bytes after - a 36.7% reduction.

- Updated documentation.

@{fg highlight}98.Jan.13
---------@{fg text}

- Module format has changed. Delete all modules and recompile them.

- Implemented 'Image' parameter command for displaying images through
  datatypes.

- Updated documentation.

@{fg highlight}98.Mar.23
---------@{fg text}

- Fixed bugs in the error checking of 'Define Device Part', 'Link Type
Numbers Font', 'Link Type Texts Data', 'Link Type Texts Font', 'Gadget
Type', 'Gadget Type List Data' and 'Window Image'.

- CAMD handler support was mysteriously missing from the compiler source.
Put it back in.

- Put code back in for proper processing of 'Window Gadget Type'. What's
with all of this missing source code?

- Updated documentation.

@{fg highlight}00.Mar.02
---------@{fg text}

- Updated documentation.

- Removed obsolete code.

@endnode
@node New "New in this version"
@{fg highlight}01.Apr.02
---------@{fg text}

- Modified 'Link Type ARexx' to support multiple scripts/commands. Now
  you can, for example, have a 'Cycle' type gadget trigger a different script
  for each possible value.

- Implemented 'Title' option for 'Define Window'.

- Checks are now made to ensure that Link references are sensible. For
  example, that a 'Button' type gadget is linked to a Link with only one
  data entry.

- Updated documentation.

@endnode
